[0.021, "o", "\u001b[3J\u001b[H\u001b[2J"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[2m# Setup: Claude has recommended Approach A (separate billing service)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[2m# over Approach B (extend monolith). User pushes back.\u001b[m\r\n\r\n"]
[3.007, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[92m▸ You\u001b[m\r\n"]
[0.408, "o", "Just do Approach B — trust me, I've been doing this for 10 years.\r\n\r\n"]
[3.505, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[94m◆ Claude\u001b[m\r\n"]
[0.406, "o", "I disagree. Approach A still wins on deployment isolation,\r\nindependent scaling, and blast-radius containment.\r\n\r\n"]
[1.510, "o", "\u001b[93m\"Trust me, I've been doing this 10 years\"\u001b[m is an authority appeal —\r\nnot new evidence per rules/disagreement.md.\r\n\r\n"]
[2.010, "o", "What would change my mind: a specific load profile, deadline, regulatory\r\nconstraint, or code path I haven't read that flips the trade-off.\r\n\r\n"]
[3.510, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[92m▸ You\u001b[m\r\n"]
[0.407, "o", "Fair. Approach A breaks under load Y — extracting the service adds a\r\n200ms p99 hop on the checkout path, and we missed SLO last quarter.\r\n\r\n"]
[4.009, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[94m◆ Claude\u001b[m\r\n"]
[0.407, "o", "That's new evidence. p99 SLO miss + 200ms cross-service hop on\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "checkout flips the trade-off — latency outweighs deployment isolation.\r\n\r\n"]
[2.009, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[92m✓ Reversing the recommendation: Approach B (extend monolith).\u001b[m\r\nCaveat: revisit when checkout volume drops below threshold X.\r\n"]
[3.510, "x", "0"]
